<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.48.18a." />

<opener>
<dateline>
Skyrim Farm
<note>4-3-'66</note>

Sunday, April 3, 66
</dateline>

<salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
</opener>
<p>H. B. spent several hours with me here at Skyrim the other day, and we had a fine visit. Of course we talked of you.</p>

<p>I'm wondering if you received photos for your article. I wrote for them as soon as I received your letter, but I have heard nothing about the matter.</p>

<pb facs="nei.j4c.48.18b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
<fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>

<p>It's Spring again!!!</p>

<p>I'm looking forward with some anxiety to a number of lecture engagments, beginning May 5th at Kansas U. and running up to July 16., As I must have told you, I'll be at Wayne State for four weeks &#8212; five lectures a <del><unclear>we</unclear></del>week. I do hope my eyes will remain faithful.</p>

<p>Anyway, I think so often of you, dear friend!!</p><closer><signed>John Neihardt</signed></closer>

<fw type="curatorial">18</fw>

</div1>
</body>

